						<summary>

						<p>On the seventh pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 10: 916-17 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records the gift of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp to the Āḷvār at Tirumaṟaikkāḍu by Bāradāyan Uḻundan Kaṇḍan of Kumāramaṅgalam.</p>						

